1. Uninstall any nvidia drivers remaining by following the steps here: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/56431461/how-to-remove-cuda-completely-from-ubuntu

2. Install Cuda 11.8 toolkit by using this link: https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-11-8-0-download-archive?target_os=Linux&target_arch=x86_64&Distribution=Ubuntu&target_version=22.04&target_type=runfile_local

3. Add these lines in ~/.bashrc file:
# CUDA Toolkit 11.8
if [ -z $LD_LIBRARY_PATH ]; then
  LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/cuda-11.8/lib64
else
  LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:/usr/local/cuda-11.8/lib64
fi
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH

export PATH="/usr/local/cuda-11.8/bin:$PATH"

4. Install pytorch 2.0.0 with CUDA 11.8 with: "pip3 install torch torchvision torchaudio --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu118"

5. Install pytorch-sparse and pytorch-scatter following the github

6. Install pytorch-geometric using pip on the github

7. Run the setup using this command: python setup.py install

